(775, 1, '2010-11-27 01:37:39', 'note_add', 1, '{"date_default":"2010-11-26","subject":"System breakdown","task":"234","topic":"4","date":"","date_hour":"hour","date_minute":"hour","description":"Here\\u2019s a breakdown of the code:\\r\\n \\r\\n1. Get all active brands from db\\r\\n2. Deactivate all brands in db\\r\\n3. Deactivate all users in db\\r\\n4. Loop over each line in the csv dealer file\\r\\n            4.1 Format each line to conform to \\"dealers\\" table\\r\\n            4.2 Loop over each brands (step #1)\\r\\n                        4.2.1 Create array of brands users belong to\\r\\n                        4.2.2 If the brand title is \\"Kaman Music\\" or if the \\"dealer code\\" is in the current csv line add the dealer to brand array\\r\\n                        4.2.3 Add user or update existing\\r\\n \\r\\nIt appears that just replacing the hard coding of Kaman with a database query should solve the current issue and prevent this issue from happening the next time they change their name (as we discussed earlier).\\r\\n \\r\\nThe file in question is (from the site document root):\\r\\n\\/dealer_import.php (line 212)\\r\\n \\r\\nThere\\u2019s another file that has the same hard coding but, from the file name at least, it doesn\\u2019t appear it\\u2019s an active file.\\r\\n\\/dealer_import.old.php (line 213)\\r\\n \\r\\nAs to fixing things it seems pretty straightforward; update the code and test the upload to make sure we\\u2019re all good. This does present a small problem in that I\\u2019m not entirely sure how the process should work. If possible, can I get a copy of the latest import data file as well as instructions on how the import process works (urls, process, etc)? Once I have that though testing and fixing should trivial.\\r\\n","project":"64","company":"22","company_id":"22","project_id":"64","task_id":"234"}', 22, 64, 234, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2010-11-27 01:37:39', '2010-11-27 01:37:39'),
