(1157, 1, '2012-03-24 22:11:05', 'project_add', 1, '{"start_date_default":"2012-03-24","end_date_default":"2012-03-24","name":"eat-art.org","company_id":"32","status":"3","priority":"3","type":"2","description":"\\u2022\\tOpen Gallery - Membership Management\\r\\no\\tUsers can register for an account (Facebook\\/Twitter Connect)\\r\\no\\tUsers can login and add\\/edit up to 15 pieces of art\\r\\no\\tUsers can also upload \\/ add \\/ delete images of themselves\\r\\no\\tUser can manage all their personal info, including resetting password, etc.\\r\\no\\tUser add their birthday with year to determine age for youth artists - it would also determine where the system shows their gallery (open or youth). \\r\\no\\tWhen user uploads picture, depending on dimensions\\/size of image, certain sizes are available for sale. \\r\\n\\u2022\\tArtist Main Page - Listing of All Artists (Featured, Open and Youth)\\r\\no\\tAll three sections will be formatted similarly.  Each page will have thumbnails of each artist.  If you click on the thumbnail, it goes to the artist''s page where there''s information about the artist and other thumbnails of that artist''s other art pieces.  Clicking on the art thumbnail on the artists page will then allow the user to purchase the art with the current CartThrob ecommerce functionality.\\r\\no\\tLayout - Similar to http:\\/\\/500px.com\\/popular where it would be 4 across and 5 rows (so a little bigger than current square images) and would display one pic of the artists gallery (their first) and have the artist name overlayed on the bottom of the pic - this would link to their artist gallery page.\\r\\no\\tThis would be sorted by total meals sold from their gallery. If total meals sold is the same (i.e. 0), then the second sort value would be most recently added artists.\\r\\no\\tYouth Artist Main Page - display banner with their age (under 18).\\r\\n\\u2022\\tArtist Profile Gallery Page\\r\\no\\tSimilar to what we have currently (i.e. http:\\/\\/eat-art.org\\/art\\/artist\\/todd_clark), but adding profile pic, and meal count badget (total meals sold from their gallery)\\r\\no\\tFirst picture would be their thumbnail or cover image for the artist main page.\\r\\no\\tsame layout - 5 across and 5 rows\\r\\no\\tsomewhere on this page, a simple button that says \\u201cflag as inappropriate\\u201d \\u2026 it would just email us to look at their gallery page and see if we need to delete a pic or the whole artist for spam.\\r\\n\\u2022\\tNavigation Changes\\r\\no\\tFeatured Artists\\r\\no\\tOpen Artists\\r\\no\\tYouth Art\\r\\no\\tApparel\\r\\n\\u2022\\tBackend\\r\\no\\tArtist channel - distinguish between Artist (Open), Featured Artist, Youth Artist\\r\\no\\tTotal Meal Count - automated \\u2026 when purchase order is complete, update meal count (main one and artist gallery one)\\r\\no\\tWe need the link of the full-res uploaded image to download and order the print in the order entry on backend so that when we go to order, it will be easily downloadable.\\r\\n","start_date":"2012-03-24","end_date":"2012-04-30","creator":"1"}', 0, 84, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2012-03-24 22:11:05', '2012-03-24 22:11:05'),
